the Gurjar Leader Colonel Kirori Mal Bainsla. All the news papers and media declared this news of banned on this movie on 17 and 18 October 2014.\n|-\n| 2014\n| ''[[No Fire Zone]]''\n| The [[Sri Lankan Civil War]] documentary was not allowed for public screening by the Censor Board. Director [[Callum Macrae]] decided to release the film on the internet to circumvent the ban.<ref name=\"no_fire_zone\">{{Cite news |url=http://www.hindustantimes.com/entertainment/worldcinema/film-on-sri-lankan-war-banned-in-india/article1-1187291.aspx |title=Film on Sri Lankan war banned in India |date=23 February 2014 |work=[[Hindustan Times]] |access-date=27 February 2014 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20140223214811/http://www.hindustantimes.com/entertainment/worldcinema/film-on-sri-lankan-war-banned-in-india/article1-1187291.aspx |archive-date=23 February 2014}}</ref>\n|-\n| 2014\n| ''[[Kaum De Heere]]''\n| The film was banned by the central government after the [[Intelligence Bureau (India)|Intelligence Bureau]] had warned that the film may cause communal tensions. The film glorified the assassins of former Prime Minister [[Indira Gandhi]].<ref name=\"KaumDeHeere\">{{Cite news |url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/india/Centre-blocks-release-of-controversial-film-on-Indira-Gandhis-assassins-Kaum-de-Heere/articleshow/40606687.cms |title=Centre blocks release of controversial film on Indira Gandhi\u2019s assassins \u2018Kaum de Heere\u2019 |date=21 August 2014 |work=[[The Times of India]] |access-date=8 January 2015 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141121153206/http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/india/Centre-blocks-release-of-controversial-film-on-Indira-Gandhis-assassins-Kaum-de-Heere/articleshow/40606687.cms |archive-date=21 November 2014}}</ref>\n|-\n| 2015\n| ''[[Fifty Shades of Grey (film)|Fifty Shades of Grey]]''\n| The film was not given a rating by the Censor Board, even after voluntary cuts by the distributor.<ref name