ghters/532048-3.html |title=Banning India's daughters |last=Vohra, Anchal |date=4 March 2015 |website=[[IBNLive]] |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150306131724/http://ibnlive.in.com/news/banning-indias-daughters/532048-3.html |archive-date=6 March 2015 |access-date=5 March 2015}}</ref><ref name=TriedToSupress /> including remarks defending the rape<ref name=\"TriedToSupress\">{{Cite news |url=https://www.independent.co.uk/news/world/asia/indias-daughter-how-india-tried-to-suppress-the-bbc-delhi-gangrape-documentary-10088890.html |title=India's Daughter: How India tried to suppress the BBC Delhi gang-rape documentary |last=Withnall, Adam |date=5 March 2015 |work=[[The Independent]] |access-date=5 March 2015 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150307065348/http://www.independent.co.uk/news/world/asia/indias-daughter-how-india-tried-to-suppress-the-bbc-delhi-gangrape-documentary-10088890.html |archive-date=7 March 2015}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.theguardian.com/world/2015/mar/05/delhi-gang-rape-documentary-airs-early-on-bbc-following-objections |title=Delhi gang-rape documentary airs early on BBC following objections |last=Rawlinson, Kevin |date=5 March 2015 |access-date=5 March 2015 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150307040959/http://www.theguardian.com/world/2015/mar/05/delhi-gang-rape-documentary-airs-early-on-bbc-following-objections |archive-date=7 March 2015 |publisher=The Guardian}}</ref> which drew public outcry in India when the film was shown.<ref>{{Cite news |url=https://www.independent.co.uk/arts-entertainment/tv/news/indias-daughter-bbc-four-documentary-provokes-outrage-on-twitter-10086622.html |title=India's Daughter: BBC Four documentary provokes outrage on Twitter |last=Gander, Kashmira |date=4 March 2015 |work=[[The Independent]] |access-date=5 March 2015 |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150306023217/http://www.independent.co.uk/arts-