me at number 18.<ref>{{cite news|title=Forbes Korea's '2015 Korea Power Celebrity 40.'|url=http://jmagazine.joins.com/forbes/view/305259|accessdate=5 March 2015|work=Forbes|date=23 February 2015}}</ref> That same month, the group was chosen as one of the \"Best 3 New Artists (Asia)\" at the [[Japan Gold Disc Awards]], held by the [[Recording Industry Association of Japan]].<ref>{{cite news|title=The 2015 Japan Golden Disc Award winners are...|url=http://www.sbs.com.au/popasia/blog/2015/03/03/2015-japan-golden-disc-award-winners-are|accessdate=5 March 2015|publisher=SBS|date=3 March 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=[THE JAPAN GOLD DISC AWARD 2015]|url=http://golddisc.jp/award/29/index.html#gd29_07|website=golddisc.jp|publisher=RIAJ|accessdate=5 March 2015}}</ref>\n\nApink headlined their first overseas concert \"Pink Paradise\" in Singapore at [[Singapore Expo|The MAX Pavilion]] on March 22.<ref name=\"singapore\">{{cite news|title=Apink to hold concert in Singapore|url=http://kpopherald.koreaherald.com/view.php?ud=201503101403095194327_2|publisher=KpopHerald|date=10 March 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=A Pink to Hold its First Exclusive Overseas Concert in Singapore|url=http://mwave.interest.me/enewsworld/en/article/89525/a-pink-to-hold-its-first-exclusive-overseas-concert-in-singapore|publisher=Mwave|date=March 18, 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.kpopstarz.com/articles/187625/20150327/a-pink-paradise-press-conference-singapore.htm|title=A Pink Charm Like White Angels At Pink Paradise Press Conference In Singapore|publisher=Kpopstarz|date=March 27, 2015|accessdate=29 March 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://kpopherald.koreaherald.com/view.php?ud=201503231707312085704_2|title=Apink pulls off Singapore concert with fervor|publisher=KpopHerald|date=March 23, 2015|accessdate=29 March 2015}}</ref> They appeared at the Korean Times Music Festival in Los Angeles in May, Music Bank event in [[Hanoi]], [[Vietnam]] and performed \"Pink Paradise in [[Shanghai]].<ref>{{cite news|title=EXO, SHINee to join KBS2 'Music Bank in Hanoi'|url=http://www.kpopherald.com/view.php?ud=201502241441576620969_2|publisher=KpopHerald|date=24 February 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=A Pink, Bada, Im Tae-kyung coming to Hollywood Bowl for KTMF|url=http://www.koreatimesus.com/a-pink-bada-im-tae-kyung-coming-to-hollywood-bowl-for-ktmf-2015/|publisher=KoreaTimesUS|date=10 March 2015}}</ref>\n\nApink released a single entitled \"Promise U\" on April 19, written by Jeong Eun-ji to commemorate the group's fourth anniversary.<ref>{{cite news|author1=Lim Jeong-yeo|title=Apink releases 'Promise U' and behind-the-scene shots|url=http://www.kpopherald.com/view.php?ud=201504191429487525600_2|accessdate=May 15, 2015|work=[[K-Pop Herald]]|date=April 19, 2015}}</ref> A Japanese version of \"Luv\" was released on May 20 as their third single, with \"Good Morning Baby\" as the B-side.<ref>{{cite web|title=3rd\u30b7\u30f3\u30b0\u30eb\u300cLUV -Japanese Ver.-\u300d\u8a73\u7d30\u767a\u8868\uff01|url=http://apink-mobile.com/various/notice/2015/03/09/299/|accessdate=13 March 2015}}</ref> They performed the song for the first time at the \"Girls Award 2015 Spring/Summer\" in Tokyo on April 29 ahead of the release.<ref name=\"oriconmrchu\"/> The group also held release events in four cities, Tokyo, [[Sapporo]], [[Okayama]] and Osaka as part of promotional event.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.allkpop.com/article/2015/05/a-pink-to-release-luv-in-japan|title=A Pink to release 'LUV' in Japan {{!}} allkpop.com|date=2015-05-14|website=Allkpop|access-date=2016-06-25}}</ref>\n\nOn July 16, the group released their second full-length album, ''Pink Memory'', along with the title track \"Remember\".<ref>{{cite news|url=http://news.donga.com/3/all/20150716/72509851/3|script-title=ko:\uc5d0\uc774\ud551\ud06c '\ub9ac\uba64\ubc84' \uacf5\uac1c\u2026 '\uc139\uc2dc \ucf58\uc149\ud2b8? \uc6b0\ub9b0 \ubb34\uc870\uac74 \uccad\uc21c~'|work=DongA|date=July 16, 2015|accessdate=18 July 2015|language=ko}}</ref> On August 22 and 23, the group held their second concert \"Pink Island\"  at Jamsil Indoor Stadium, after which they began overseas activities including a fan meeting in [[Thailand]], hold their first concert tour in Japan, and a performance at MTV World Stage in [[Malaysia]] 2015.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.kpopstarz.com/articles/224933/20150729/a-pink-concert.htm|title=Tickets For A Pink's 2nd Solo Concert 'Pink Island' In High Demand|date=July 29, 2015|accessdate=July 29, 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://kpopfighting.com/2015/09/04/a-pink-successfully-kicks-off-their-japan-concert-tour-in-nagoya/ |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2015-09-07 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150907190830/http://kpopfighting.com/2015/09/04/a-pink-successfully-kicks-off-their-japan-concert-tour-in-nagoya/ |archivedate=September 7, 2015 |df=mdy-all }}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://worldstage.mtvasia.com/news/mtv-reveals-first-wave-of-performers-with-apink-and-sekai-no-owari-to-perform-for-the-first-time-at-mtv-world-stage-malaysia/ |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2015-09-07 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20151001104939/http://worldstage.mtvasia.com/news/mtv-reveals-first-wave-of-performers-with-apink-and-sekai-no-owari-to-perform-for-the-first-time-at-mtv-world-stage-malaysia/ |archivedate=October 1, 2015 |df=mdy-all }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.nationthailand.com/life/30268152|title=Apink ramps up the charm for 'pink pandas'}}</ref> On August 26 the group released their first Japanese full-length album ''[[Pink Season (Apink album)|Pink Season]]''.\n\nIn November 2015, Apink announced their first tour in [[North America]] and are scheduled to perform in [[Vancouver]], [[Dallas]], [[San Francisco]] and [[Los Angeles]].<ref>{{Cite news|last=Benjamin|first=Jeff|title=Apink Announces U.S. Tour, First for a K-Pop Girl Group Since 2012|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/k-town/6770260/apink-pink-memory-america-tour|website=Billboard|date=November 21, 2015|accessdate=December 14, 2015}}</ref> The group's fourth Japanese single Sunday Monday was released on December 9, along with the Japanese version of Petal as B-side track.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.koreaboo.com/video/apink-releases-sunday-monday-pv-upcoming-winter-japanese-single/|title=Apink releases \"Sunday Monday\" PV for upcoming winter Japanese single|date=2015-11-19|website=Koreaboo|access-date=2016-06-25}}</ref> At the end of 2015, Apink received Top 10 for [[MelOn Music Awards]].<ref>{{Cite news|last=Buhain|first=James|title=Big Bang, EXO Take Home Top Honors At 2015 MelOn Music Awards + Full List Of Winners|url=http://www.kpopstarz.com/articles/254471/20151107/melon-music-awards-2015-winners.htm|website=KpopStarz|date=November 7, 2015|accessdate=March 18, 2016}}</ref> The group closed the year as the second best-selling girl group of 2015 with sales of both Pink LUV and Pink Memory albums.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://koreatimes.co.kr/www/news/culture/2015/12/135_193850.html|title=Girls' Generation gets 'A+' for their work|date=2015-12-23|website=The Korea Times|access-date=2016-07-06}}</ref>\n\nApink started their North American tour on January 5 in Vancouver, followed by shows in Dallas, San Francisco and Los Angeles. The same month, they received Bonsang for [[Seoul Music Awards]] and Disk Bonsang for [[Golden Disk Awards]].<ref>{{Cite news|title=Winners of 25th Seoul Music Awards|url=http://www.soompi.com/2016/01/14/winners-of-25th-seoul-music-awards/|website=Soompi|date=January 14, 2016|accessdate=March 18, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|title=Winners of the 30th Golden Disc Awards, Day Two|url=http://www.soompi.com/2016/01/21/winners-of-the-30th-golden-disc-awards-day-two/|website=Soompi|date=January 21, 2016|accessdate=March 18, 2016}}</ref> On January 24, the group was invited to attend KKBOX Music Awards in Taiwan.<ref>{{Cite news|last=Kim|first=Yu-jin|title=Apink the only K-pop star to attend Taiwan music awards|url=http://kpopherald.koreaherald.com/view.php?ud=201512281719175075934_2|website=KoreaHerald|date=December 28, 2015|accessdate=March 18, 2016}}</ref> On February 25, the group released the music video to their first original Japanese song called \"Brand New days\". The song is the opening theme song for anime [[Rilu Rilu Fairilu]] ~Yousei No Door~.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.crunchyroll.com/anime-news/2016/02/04-1/korean-girls-idol-group-apink-to-perform-op-song-for-tv-anime-rilu-rilu-fairilu|title=Korean Girls Idol Group Apink to Perform OP Song for TV Anime \"Rilu Rilu Fairilu\"|last=Komatsu|first=Mikikazu|date=2016-02-04|website=Cruchyroll|access-date=2016-06-25}}</ref> The group performed at 10th [[Asian Film Awards]] on March 17.<ref>{{Cite news|title=A Pink is the only K-pop group to perform at 10th Asian Film Awards!|url=http://www.allkpop.com/article/2016/03/a-pink-is-the-only-k-pop-group-to-perform-at-10th-asian-film-awards|website=AllKpop|date=March 3, 2016|accessdate=March 18, 2016}}</ref> On April 2, the group performed a mini concert \"Pink Memory Day\" in Singapore.<ref>{{Cite news|title=A Pink Return To Singapore In April For Mini-Concert And Fan Meeting|url=http://www.kpopstarz.com/articles/268840/20160215/apink-pink-memory-singapore.htm|website=KpopStarz|date=February 15, 2016|accessdate=April 9, 2016}}</ref> On April 19, Apink released a digital single entitled \"The Wave\", written by Park Cho-rong to celebrate their 5th anniversary along with a photobook called \"Girls' Sweet Repose\".<ref>{{Cite news|title=A Pink thank their fans on their 5th anniversary with 'Wave'|url=http://www.allkpop.com/article/2016/04/a-pink-thank-their-fans-on-their-5th-anniversary-with-wave|website=AllKpop|date=April 18, 2016|accessdate=April 21, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.allkpop.com/article/2016/04/a-pink-to-release-a-special-fan-song-and-photobook-on-the-19th-for-their-5th-anniversary|title=A Pink to release a special fan song and photobook on the 19th for their 5th anniversary! {{!}} allkpop.com|last=|first=|date=2016-04-04|website=AllKpop|access-date=2016-07-09}}</ref>\n\n[[File:Apink at Korea Sale Festa Opening Ceremony, 30 September 2016 06.png|thumb|250px|right|Apink at Korea Sale Festa Opening Ceremony, 30 September 2016]]\nApink performed alongside international acts [[OneRepublic]], [[Far East Movement]], [[Bebe Rexha]] and [[Philippines]]'s artists [[Gary Valenciano]] and his son [[Gabriel Valenciano|Gabriel]], and love team [[James Reid (entertainer)|James Reid]] and [[Nadine Lustre]] for MTV Music Evolution in [[Manila]] on 24 June.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.philstar.com/entertainment/2016/06/25/1596551/artists-all-ages-genres-unite-mtv-music-evolution|title=Artists of all ages, genres unite at MTV Music Evolution|last=Jimenez|first=Joyce|date=2016-06-25|website=philstar.com|access-date=2016-06-25}}</ref> Apink held their second Japan concert tour in July, kicking off in Sapporo on July 7.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://mwave.interest.me/enewsworld/en/article/106765/apink-holds-another-successful-concert-in-japan-best-kpop|title=KPOP NEWS - Apink Holds Another Successful Concert in Japan {{!}} Mwave|last=|first=|date=2016-07-08|website=mwave.interest.me|access-date=2016-07-09}}</ref> They performed in front of 20,000 fans throughout six concerts in five cities and was scheduled to release their 6th Japanese single, ''Summer Time'', on August 3.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.newsen.com/news_view.php?uid=201607240935209110|title=\uc5d0\uc774\ud551\ud06c, \u65e5 5\uac1c\ub3c4\uc2dc \ud22c\uc5b4 2\ub9cc\uc5ec\uba85 \ud32c\ub4e4\uacfc '\uc0ac\uc694\ub098\ub77c'|last=|first=|date=2016-07-24|website=Newsen|access-date=2016-07-24}}</ref> To promote the song, Apink held release events in seven different cities, from 1 to 7 August, starting in [[Fukuoka]], followed by events in [[Hiroshima]], [[Nagoya]], Osaka, [[Kobe]], Tokyo and [[Niigata, Niigata|Niigata]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://entertain.naver.com/read?oid=215&aid=0000484449|title=\uc5d0\uc774\ud551\ud06c, \u65e5 \uc2f1\uae00 \ubc1c\ub9e4 \uae30\ub150 '1\uc77c 1\ub3c4\uc2dc' \ub9b4\ub808\uc774 \uc774\ubca4\ud2b8 \uac1c\ucd5c|last=|first=|date=2016-08-02|website=Naver|access-date=2016-08-05}}</ref>\n\nApink released their third full-length Korean album, [[Pink Revolution (album)|Pink Revolution]], on September 26, 2016, following a hiatus of one year and two months, the group's longest since debut. The title track, \"Only One\" (\ub0b4\uac00 \uc124\ub810 \uc218 \uc788\uac8c), was used to promote the album along with B-tracks \"Boom Pow Love\" and \"Ding Dong\".<ref>{{cite web|url=http://news.donga.com/3/all/20160926/80481089/2|title=\uc5d0\uc774\ud551\ud06c, \uc2e0\uace1 '\ub0b4\uac00 \uc124\ub810 \uc218 \uc788\uac8c'\ub85c \uc628\ub77c\uc778 \ucc28\ud2b8 \ud729\uc4f8\uc5b4\u2026'\uc74c\uc6d0\uac15\uc790' \uc800\ub825 \uc785\uc99d|date=September 26, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://isplus.live.joins.com/news/article/article.asp?total_id=20638622&cloc=rss%7Cisplus%7Centertainment|title=[\ud3ec\ud1a0\uc5d4]\uc5d0\uc774\ud551\ud06c '\uc608\uc068 \ud55c\uac00\ub4dd \ucc44\uc6b4 \ubb34\ub300'|last=|first=|date=2016-09-26|work=|access-date=2016-10-09|via=}}</ref> On the same day, they held a showcase which was broadcast live through V-live. Apink worked with [[Black Eyed Pilseung]] for the title track, as well as well-known producers such as Shinsadong Tiger and [[Dsign Music]] for the B-sides.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.soompi.com/2016/09/12/apink-works-black-eyed-pilseung-title-track-pink-revolution-album/|title=Apink Works With Black Eyed Pilseung For Title Track Of \"Pink Revolution\" Album|last=|first=|date=2016-09-12|website=Soompi|access-date=2016-10-09}}</ref> \"Only One\" topped seven music charts in Korea just a few hours after it was released. During the showcase, leader Cho-Rong stated that ''Pink Revolution'' would incorporate a new sense of Apink's growth and maturity since debut, while Eun-ji explained that Apink will begin to focus on making complex and beautiful music, rather than tracks that \"are simply fun and catchy.\" <ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.allkpop.com/article/2016/09/a-pink-wanted-to-showcase-that-they-matured-through-new-album|title=A Pink wanted to showcase that they matured through new album {{!}} allkpop.com|access-date=2016-09-27}}</ref> Apink promoted \"Only One\" and ''Pink Revolution'' for nearly a month, and the album has since sold 50,000+ copies in South Korea.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.gaonchart.co.kr/|title=\uad6d\ub0b4 \ub300\ud45c \uc74c\uc545 \ucc28\ud2b8 \uac00\uc628\ucc28\ud2b8!|website=www.gaonchart.co.kr|access-date=2016-12-02}}</ref>\n\nIn November 2016, Apink began their \"Pink Aurora\" Asia Tour, performing at numerous destinations throughout eastern Asia including Taiwan and Singapore. Plan A Entertainment also announced Apink's 3rd Korean concert \"Pink Party,\" which took place in Seoul on December 17 and 18. After this announcement, tickets sold out in just over two minutes. Also during this time, Apink returned to Japan to promote their upcoming second Japanese album, \"Pink Doll,\" which is set to be released in Japan on December 21.\n\nOn November 30, Plan A Entertainment announced through Naver that Apink would be returning on December 15 with their first special album, ''Dear,'' despite rigorous activities and promotions throughout the end of 2016. Plan A stated that the album would commend the unwavering love and invaluable support from their fans since debut. ''Dear'' has five new original songs, three of which are duets sung and written exclusively by pairs of members. A music video for the album's title track, \"Cause You're My Star,\" was uploaded on YouTube by 1theK and Apink's official channel. The album also included instrumentals and ballad versions of Apink's previous hits including \"Mr. Chu,\" \"NoNoNo,\" \"Luv,\" and \"April 19th\".<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.allkpop.com/article/2016/11/a-pink-to-return-with-their-first-special-album-soon|title=A Pink to return with their first special album soon! {{!}} allkpop.com|newspaper=allkpop|access-date=2016-12-02}}</ref>\n\n=== 2017-present: International recognition of fame and worldwide success ===\n[[File:170528 Mercedes Benz Donatic & Race Event Part 2 (41).jpg|left|thumb|250px|Apink performs at the Mercedes Benz Donatic & Race Event in May 2017]]\nOn March 21, Apink released their seventh Japanese single, \"Bye Bye\". Eun-Ji's second mini album, ''The Space'', and its title track, \"The Spring\", were released on April 10.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.allkpop.com/article/2017/04/a-pinks-eunji-begins-the-teasers-for-her-solo-comeback|title=A Pink's Eunji begins the teasers for her solo comeback {{!}} allkpop.com|work=allkpop|access-date=2017-07-11}}</ref> On April 19, Apink released another fan song, \"Always\". Eun-ji's first solo concert took place on June 3\u20135.<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.allkpop.com/article/2017/05/a-pinks-eunji-to-hold-her-first-ever-solo-concert|title=A Pink's Eunji to hold her first ever solo concert {{!}} allkpop.com|work=allkpop|access-date=2017-07-11}}</ref>\n\nOn June 26, ''Pink UP'' was released, along with the single \"Five\", written by [[Shinsadong Tiger]]. In its first week of release, ''Pink UP'' topped the [[Gaon Album Chart]], the first since ''[[Pink Luv]]''.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://gaonchart.co.kr/main/section/chart/album.gaon?nationGbn=T|title=\uad6d\ub0b4 \ub300\ud45c \uc74c\uc545 \ucc28\ud2b8 \uac00\uc628\ucc28\ud2b8!|website=gaonchart.co.kr|access-date=2017-07-11}}</ref> \"Five\" peaked at number 4 on the digital chart.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://gaonchart.co.kr/main/section/chart/online.gaon?nationGbn=T&serviceGbn=ALL|title=\uad6d\ub0b4 \ub300\ud45c \uc74c\uc545 \ucc28\ud2b8 \uac00\uc628\ucc28\ud2b8!|website=gaonchart.co.kr|access-date=2017-07-11}}</ref>\n\nApink released the Japanese single \"Motto GO!GO!\" on July 25 and promoted the song by holding their third Japanese tour, '3 Years' - performing in Kobe on the 22nd, Nagoya on the 26th, and Yokohama on the 30th of July.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.allkpop.com/article/2017/07/a-pink-wraps-up-3rd-japanese-tour-3-years|title=A Pink wraps up 3rd Japanese tour '3 Years' {{!}} allkpop.com|work=allkpop|access-date=2018-08-06}}</ref> As a collaboration with labelmates Huh Gak and Victon, Apink released \"Oasis\" on August 3, a remake of 2007 [[Brown Eyed Girls]] song.<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.allkpop.com/article/2017/08/a-pink-huh-gak-victon-enjoy-a-summer-oasis-in-new-mv|title=A Pink, Huh Gak, & VICTON enjoy a summer 'Oasis' in new MV! {{!}} allkpop.com|work=allkpop|access-date=2018-08-06}}</ref>\n\nStarting in August, Apink began their \"Pink Up\" Asia Tour, performing in Hong Kong, Bangkok and Taipei. In October, Apink returned to Japan to promote their ninth Japanese single, \"Orion, and later that month also announced the closing of their Japanese fan club 'Panda Japan'.<ref>{{Cite web | url=https://www.allkpop.com/article/2017/10/a-pink-sing-about-orion-in-full-japanese-comeback-mv | title=A Pink sing about 'Orion' in full Japanese comeback MV}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web | url=https://www.allkpop.com/article/2017/10/a-pink-to-officially-close-japanese-fan-club-panda-japan | title=A Pink to officially close Japanese fan club 'Panda Japan'}}</ref> At the Asia Artist Awards on November 15, Apink won the 'Best Celebrity Award'.\n\n\n[[File:180324 \uc804\ub77c\uace050\uc8fc\ub144 \uae30\ub150\ud589\uc0ac \uc5d0\uc774\ud551\ud06c part.1 (1).jpg|right|thumb|250px|Apink in March 2018]]\nApink held their fourth Korean concert ''Pink Space'' in Seoul on January 12 and 13. The concert, which was announced in December, had sold out tickets three minutes after its announcement. In celebration of their seventh anniversary, Apink released single \"Miracle\" and a photobook on April 19, followed by a fan meeting held on April 21.\n\nOn July 2, Apink released their seventh mini album ''[[One & Six]]''. The title track, \"I'm So Sick\" ({{ko-hhrm|1\ub3c4 \uc5c6\uc5b4}}), was used to promote the album along with B-track \"Alright\". Once again, Apink worked with common collaborator Black Eyed Pilseung for the title track, who had previously produced \"Only One\". With this comeback, Apink took on a different direction conceptually, with a bolder image and a more sophisticated sound. \"I'm So Sick\" topped several music charts in South Korea after its release. The album itself topped the Gaon chart and led Apink to reach their highest-ever position on Billboard's World Albums chart at No. 11. The success of the song and album further led to Apink making their debut on Billboard's Social 50 chart, opening at No. 39.<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/k-town/8465258/apink-one-and-six-world-albums-social-50-chart-im-so-sick|title=Apink Score Highest Entry on World Albums Chart to Date, Debut on Social 50|author=Jeff Benjamin|date=July 13, 2018|accessdate=August 6, 2018|publisher=[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]}}</ref> Billboard have chosen the title track as one of 20 Best K-Pop Songs of 2018, noting that \"it felt a bit meta -- as the six-member girl group swapped out their girlish image for something far more compelling.\".<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/events/year-in-music-2018/8490486/best-k-pop-songs-2018-top-20|title=The 20 Best K-pop Songs of 2018: Critics' Picks|website=Billboard|access-date=2019-01-06}}</ref>\n\nIn August, Apink embarked on another Asia tour, visiting Hong Kong, Kuala Lumpur, Jakarta, Singapore, Tokyo and Taipei. On December 1, Apink received the Top 10 Artists award at the [[MelOn Music Awards]] for their song \"I'm So Sick\".<ref>{{cite news|script-title=ko:MMA TOP 10 \uc218\uc0c1\ud55c \uc5d0\uc774\ud551\ud06c \ub0b4\ub144 1\uc6d4 \ucef4\ubc31 \ud655\uc815\uc9c0\uc5b4, 6\uac1c\uc6d4\ub9cc\uc758 \ucef4\ubc31\uc5d0 \ud32c\ub4e4 \ud658\ud638|url=http://medicalreport.kr/news/view/65393| accessdate=February 20, 2019|date=December 4, 2019|language=ko}}</ref>\n[[File:190120 Apink Mini Fan Meeting.jpg|left|thumb|200px|Apink in January 2019]]\nApink held their fifth Korean concert ''Pink Collection: Red and White'' in Seoul on January 12 and 13. The concert, which was announced in December, sold out all tickets three minutes after its announcement. This was followed by concert ''Apink Japan Live Pink Collection'' in Tokyo, held on February 3 and 4.\n\nOn January 7, Apink released their eighth mini album ''Percent'', along with the single \"%%(Eung Eung)\", composed  by frequent collaborator Black Eyed Pilseung and Jeon Goon. The single, which continued the new direction taken by the group with \"I'm So Sick\", topped several music charts in South Korea after its release and peaked at No. 17 on the Gaon digital chart,<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://gaonchart.co.kr/main/section/chart/online.gaon?nationGbn=T&serviceGbn=ALL&targetTime=02&hitYear=2019&termGbn=week|title=2019\ub144 02\uc8fc\ucc28 Digital Chart |website=gaonchart.co.kr|access-date=2019-01-28}}</ref> while the album reached No. 3 on the Korean chart and No. 14 on the Billboard World Albums chart.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://gaonchart.co.kr/main/section/chart/album.gaon?nationGbn=T&serviceGbn=&targetTime=02&hitYear=2019&termGbn=week|title=2019\ub144 02\uc8fc\ucc28 Album Chart|website=gaonchart.co.kr|access-date=2019-01-28}}</ref> To promote the new album, Apink performed \"%%(Eung Eung)\" on various music shows, along with B-side track \"Hug Me\", for a period of two weeks beginning on January 9.\n\nOn March 13, 2020, Play M Entertainment announced that Apink would be making a comeback some time in April.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://sports.khan.co.kr/entertainment/sk_index.html?art_id=202003132150003&sec_id=540101|title=\uc5d0\uc774\ud551\ud06c \uce21 \u201c4\uc6d4 \ucef4\ubc31\uc744 \ubaa9\ud45c\ub85c \uc900\ube44 \uc911\u201d|last=\uc218\uc815: 2020.03.13 23:14|first=\uc785\ub825: 2020 03 13 21:50|date=2020-03-13|website=sports.khan.co.kr|language=ko|access-date=2020-03-13}}</ref>\n\n==Image and musical style==\n[[File:A Pink at a fansigning event in Gwangju, 10 December 2014.jpg|right|thumb|Apink at a fan event, 2014]]\nApink's image and music style are often compared to first-generation idol girl groups [[S.E.S. (band)|S.E.S.]] and [[Fin.K.L]].<ref>{{cite news|author1=Park HyunMin|title=[Interview] A Pink Expects to Mature Naturally with Time| url=http://mwave.interest.me/enewsworld/en/article/2289/interview-a-pink-expects-to-mature-naturally-with-time|accessdate=February 9, 2015|work=enewsWorld|date=December 21, 2011}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|author1=Kang Seung-hoon|script-title=ko:\uc5d0\uc774\ud551\ud06c \"\ud551\ud074 SES \uc120\ubc30\ub4e4\ucc98\ub7fc \uba4b\uc9c4 \uac78\uadf8\ub8f9\ub420\ub798\uc694\"|trans-title=A Pink says, 'We want to become a girl group like Fin.K.L and SES.'|url=http://www.tvreport.co.kr/cindex.php?c=news&m=newsview&idx=178566| accessdate=February 9, 2015|work=TV Report|date=December 8, 2011|language=ko}}</ref> Apink has an innocent and girlish image, unusual among girl groups' sexy concepts.<ref>{{cite news|author1=Oak, Jessica|author2=Park Young Woong|title=The Root of K-Pop: The Influences of Today's Biggest Acts|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/k-town/5638224/the-root-of-k-pop-the-influences-of-todays-biggest-acts|accessdate=February 9, 2015|work=Billboard| date=August 6, 2013|quote=The six-member group Apink currently stands out from most girl groups, ones who have been attracting viewers for their skin-showing outfits and provocative dance moves. Apink's innocent, schoolgirl charms resemble first-generation girl groups such as S.E.S. and Fink.l.}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=Apink surprised after ranking 1st in 'The Show'|url=http://www.kpopherald.com/view.php?ud=201412031325533230849_2|accessdate=February 9, 2015|work=K-Pop Herald|date=December 3, 2014}}</ref> In 2012, member Oh Ha-young said, \"Other girl groups these days tend to highlight their dancing skills and sexy looks, but our concept was an innocent and pure image. I think that's why the audience felt comfortable with us\".<ref>{{cite news|title=Rookie Girl Band A Pink Have Big Hopes for 2012| url=http://english.chosun.com/site/data/html_dir/2012/01/05/2012010500580.html|accessdate=February 9, 2015|work=[[The Chosun Ilbo]]|date=January 5, 2012}}</ref> However, with releases like 2014's \"[[Pink Luv|Luv]]\" and 2015's \"[[Pink Memory|Remember]]\" group deviated, and showed a more mature and sensitive side to the group while still retaining their trademark innocence.<ref>{{cite news| author1=Park Gyu-oh|title=Creating pure image behind Apink's success|url=http://www.kpopherald.com/view.php?ud=201411251532444758005_2|accessdate=February 9, 2015|work=K-Pop Herald|date=November 25, 2014}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.kpopstarz.com/articles/243761/20151008/exclusive-a-pink-share-about-remember-their-music-journey-and-creating-new-memories-with-fans-at-mtv-worldstage-2015-in-malaysia.htm|title=A Pink Discuss Their Musical Journey And Experience As Idols During MTV World Stage In Malaysia [EXCLUSIVE]|date=2015-10-08|website=Kpopstarz|access-date=2016-06-28}}</ref>\n\nApink's music generally fits within the [[bubblegum pop]] genre, with signature cheery lyrics.<ref name=\"billboard4-14\" /> Jeff Benjamin of ''[[Billboard (magazine)|Billboard]]'' commented that \"[[Snow Pink|My My]]\" recalled early 2000s bubblegum pop, \"[[Secret Garden (Apink EP)|NoNoNo]]\" was influenced by 1980s synth-pop and \"[[Pink Luv|Luv]]\" recalls 1990s hip-hop while blending it with ballad melancholy, a fall-themed song of lost love.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Benjamin|first1=Jeff|title=Apink's 'Luv' Blends '90s Hip-Hop & Ballad Melancholy| url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/k-town/6327584/apinks-luv-mv-video|accessdate=February 9, 2015| work=Billboard| date=November 25, 2014}}</ref> \"[[Mr. Chu|Mr Chu]]\", released in spring 2014, continues a slew of Apink's trademark bubblegum series which is 'very Apink'.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/k-town/6052306/k-pop-hot-100-park-hyo-shin-edges-out-apink|title=K-Pop Hot 100: Park Hyo Shin Edges Out Apink|last=Benjamin|first=Jeff|date=2014-04-15|website=Billboard|access-date=2016-06-25}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://seoulbeats.com/2014/04/nothing-new-mr-chu/|title=Nothing New With \"Mr. Chu\"|date=2014-04-03|website=seoulbeats|access-date=2016-06-25}}</ref> Meanwhile, title track \"[[Pink Memory|Remember]]\" is a 'cheery synth-pop tune that reminisces about a love during the summertime,' and 'features a quick rhythm and vintage sound to beat the summer heat,'.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/k-town/6634592/apink-remember-mv-video|title=Apink Drop Sweet, Seasonal New Single 'Remember'|last=Benjamin|first=Jeff|date=2015-07-17|website=Billboard|access-date=2016-06-25}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://kpopherald.koreaherald.com/view.php?ud=201507131545003169916_2|title=Apink's title teaser 'Remember' revealed|date=2015-07-13|website=KpopHerald|access-date=2016-06-25}}</ref> Their 2016 title track, \"[[Pink Revolution (album)|Only One]]\" is described as mature, blending in mid tempo R&B and dance-pop with subtle hip-hop beats while song like \"[[Pink Revolution (album)|Boom Pow Love]]\" shows a far more urban-pop, energetic vibe with pulsing beats compared to their previous hits.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.fuse.tv/videos/2016/09/k-stop-podcast-episode-34|title='K-Stop' Podcast: GOT7, Apink, Crayon Pop, and Sunhwa Departs Secret|last=Benjamin|first=Jeff|date=2016-09-29|website=Fuse|access-date=2016-10-09}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=http://english.yonhapnews.co.kr/culturesports/2016/09/26/0701000000AEN20160926010200315.html|title=New LP means change, growth to Apink|newspaper=Yonhap News Agency|language=en|access-date=2016-10-09}}</ref>\n\nWith the release of 2018's \"I'm So Sick\", Apink showed a shift in their style of music, moving towards a more mature and sophisticated sound. The track, with its use of autotune, synth and house beats, and its lyrical content of having 'not even one' bit of feeling left for an ex, makes \"I'm So Sick\" a much bolder track than what Apink is known to put out.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/k-town/8463643/apink-im-so-sick-video|title=Apink Makes Bold Return With 'I'm So Sick': Watch the Music Video|last=Herman|first=Tamar|date=2018-07-02|website=Billboard|access-date=2019-02-20}}</ref> 2019's \"%%(Eung Eung)\" does much of the same. Its use of 'izzy snyths, snapping beats, and slapping percussion as the members sing about the type of person one should love' make %%(Eung Eung) another song that is a departure from much of Apink's earlier work.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/k-town/8492385/apink-eung-eung|title=Apink Makes Bold Return With 'I'm So Sick': Watch the Music Video|last=Herman|first=Tamar|date=2019-01-07|website=Billboard|access-date=2019-02-20}}</ref>\n\n==Discography==\n{{Main|Apink discography}}\n<!--Studio albums only. Everything else should go on the discography page.-->\n<!--No need to separated between Korean/Japanese here, they're a same contents, a studio albums-->\n* ''[[Une Ann\u00e9e]]'' (2012)\n* ''[[Pink Memory]]'' (2015)\n* ''[[Pink Season (Apink album)|Pink Season]]'' (2015)\n* ''[[Pink Revolution (album)|Pink Revolution]]'' (2016)\n* ''[[Pink Doll (Apink album)|Pink Doll]]'' (2016)\n* ''Pink Stories'' (2017)\n* [[One & Six (Apink album)|One & Six]]'' (2018)\n* [[Percent (Apink album)|Percent]]'' (2019)\n\n==Concerts and tours==\n===Headlining===\n\n'''Korean Tours'''\n* Pink Paradise (2015)\n* Pink Island (2015)\n* Pink Party (2016)\n* Pink Space (2018)\n* Pink Collection: Red and White (2019)\n* Welcome to Pink World (2020)\n\n'''Japan Tours'''\n* Apink 1st Live Tour \u2013 Pink Season (2015)\n* Apink 2nd Live Tour \u2013 Pink Summer (2016)\n* Apink 3rd Live Tour \u2013 3 Years (2017)\n* Apink Japan Live Pink Collection (2019)\n\n'''Asia Tours '''\n* Apink Secret Garden in Singapore \u2013 Vizit Korea (2013)\n* Pink Paradise Asia Tour (2015)\n* Apink Pink Memory Day In Singapore Mini Concert & Fan Meeting (2016)\n* Pink Aurora Asia Tour (2016-2017)\n* Pink Up Asia Tour (2017)\n* One&Six Asia Tour (2018)\n\n'''American Tours'''\n* Pink Memory: Apink North America Tour (2016)\n\n== Filmography ==\n\nApink started with a documentary program titled ''Apink News'', which aired on the cable channel TrendE for three seasons (2011\u20132012).<ref>{{cite news|title=\uc5d0\uc774\ud551\ud06c, '\uc5d0\uc774\ud551\ud06c \ub274\uc2a43'\uc11c \uc544\ub098\uc6b4\uc11c-PD\ub85c \u5927\ubcc0\uc2e0|url=http://osen.mt.co.kr/article/G1109420877|issue=June 21, 2012|publisher=Osen|accessdate=February 9, 2015}}</ref> They appeared in another reality show, ''Birth of a Family'', from 2011\u20132012.<ref name=Birth/> In 2014, Apink appeared on another reality show, [[MBC Every 1]]'s ''Showtime'', and were the subject of the third season.<ref name=\"Showtime\" />\n\n== Awards and nominations ==\n{{Main|List of awards and nominations received by Apink}}\n\nThe group has won awards at shows such as the 26th [[Golden Disc Awards]], 21st [[Seoul Music Awards]], and 13th [[Mnet Asian Music Awards]]. Their first music program win was on ''[[M Countdown]]'' on January 5, 2012, for \"My My\" from their second EP ''[[Snow Pink]]''.{{citation needed|date=January 2020}}\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist|30em}}\n\n== External links ==\n{{Commons category|Apink}}\n* {{official website|planaent.co.kr/apink|Apink Official Website}} {{in lang|ko}}\n\n{{Apink}}\n{{Plan A Entertainment}}\n{{Kakao M}}\n{{Golden Disk Awards for New Artist of the Year}}\n{{Authority control}}\n{{Portal bar|Asia|South Korea|Pop music|Music|Biography}}\n\n[[Category:Apink]]\n[[Category:2011 establishments in South Korea]]\n[[Category:EMI Group artists]]\n[[Category:Japanese-language singers of South Korea]]\n[[Category:K-pop music groups]]\n[[Category:Musical groups established in 2011]]\n[[Category:Musical groups from Seoul]]\n[[Category:Plan A Entertainment artists]]\n[[Category:South Korean dance music groups]]\n[[Category:South Korean girl groups]]\n[[Category:Universal Music Japan artists]]\n[[Category:Mnet Asian Music Award winners]]\n[[Category:Melon Music Award winners]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|South Korean girl group}}\n{{Use mdy dates|date=February 2015}}\n{{Infobox musical artist\n| name             = Apink\n| background       = group_or_band\n| image            = 180708 Sangam Fan Signing Apink.jpg\n| landscape        = yes\n| caption          = Apink in July 2018<br>(From left to right:  Na-eun, Ha-young, Nam-joo (top), Cho-rong (middle), Bo-mi, Eun-ji (bottom))\n| origin           = [[Seoul]], South Korea\n| genre            = {{hlist|[[K-pop]]|[[bubblegum pop]]|[[synthpop]]}}\n| years_active     = 2011\u2013present\n| label            = {{hlist|[[Play M Entertainment|Play M]]|[[Universal Music Group|UMG]] ([[EMI Records Japan|EMI]])|[[Cube Entertainment|Cube]]}}\n| website          = {{URL|planaent.co.kr/apink}} {{in lang|ko}}\n| current_members  = *[[Park Cho-rong]]\n* [[Yoon Bo-mi]]\n* [[Jung Eun-ji]]\n* [[Son Na-eun]]\n* [[Kim Nam-joo (singer)|Kim Nam-joo]]\n* [[Oh Ha-young]]\n| past_members     = *Hong Yoo-kyung\n}}\n'''Apink''' ({{lang-ko|\uc5d0\uc774\ud551\ud06c}}, {{lang-ja|\u30a8\u30fc\u30d4\u30f3\u30af}}) is a South Korean [[girl group]] formed by [[Play M Entertainment]] (formerly A Cube Entertainment<ref>{{cite news|url=http://entertain.naver.com/read?oid=079&aid=0002804324|title=EXID\u00b7\uc5d0\uc774\ud551\ud06c \uc18c\uc18d\uc0ac, \ub098\ub780\ud788 \uc0ac\uba85 \ubcc0\uacbd \uc65c|language=ko|publisher=entertain.naver.com/|date=2 March 2016|accessdate=2 March 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.kpopstarz.com/articles/269844/20160302/a-cube-plan-a-entertainment-name-change.htm|title=A Cube Entertainment Rebrands, Changes Name To Plan A Entertainment|publisher=kpopstarz.com|author=Kevin Fox|date=2 March 2016|accessdate=2 March 2016}}</ref> and Plan A Entertainment<ref>{{cite web |title=[\uacf5\uc2dd\uc785\uc7a5] \ud50c\ub79c\uc5d0\uc774\u00b7\ud398\uc774\ube0c \ud569\ubcd1\u2026'\ud50c\ub808\uc774 M' \uc774\ub984\uc73c\ub85c \uc0c8 \ucd9c\ubc1c |url=https://entertain.naver.com/now/read?oid=421&aid=0003908796 |website=entertain.naver.com |accessdate=March 29, 2019 |language=ko |date=March 29, 2019}}</ref>). The group debuted on April 19, 2011, with the [[extended play]] (EP) ''[[Seven Springs of Apink]]'' and with seven members: [[Park Cho-rong]], [[Yoon Bo-mi]], [[Jung Eun-ji]], [[Son Na-eun]], Hong Yoo-kyung, [[Kim Nam-joo (singer)|Kim Nam-joo]] and [[Oh Ha-young]]. Hong left the group in April 2013 to focus on her studies.\n\nSince their debut, Apink has won awards at shows such as the [[Golden Disc Awards]], the [[Seoul Music Awards]] and the [[Mnet Asian Music Awards]]. Their first music program win was on [[M Countdown]] on January 5, 2012, for \"My My\" from their second EP ''[[Snow Pink]]''. To date, Apink has released eight Korean mini-albums, three Korean studio albums and three Japanese studio albums.\n\n== History ==\n\n=== Pre-debut ===\nIn February 2011, [[Plan A Entertainment|A Cube Entertainment]] announced the first trainee for new girl group, Apink, was Son Na-eun, who was featured in [[Beast (South Korean band)|Beast]]' \"Soom\" ({{lang|ko|\uc228}}; \"Breath\"), \"Beautiful\" and \"Niga Jeil Joha\" ({{lang|ko|\ub2c8\uac00 \uc81c\uc77c \uc88b\uc544}}; \"I Like You the Best\") music videos in late 2010.<ref name=\"mwaveprofile\">{{cite web|title=Apink Profile|url=http://mwave.interest.me/kstar/193038/a-pink/video| website=Mwave|publisher=CJ E&M| accessdate=December 15, 2014}}</ref> Park Cho-rong, who appeared at the end of Beast's \"[[Shock (Beast song)|Shock]]\" Japanese music video, joined next, as the group's leader.<ref name=pastelcolors>{{cite news|author1=Kim Yoon-mi|title=A Pink shows seven pastel colors|url=http://www.koreaherald.com/view.php?ud=20110714000803|accessdate=December 15, 2014| work=The Korea Herald|date=July 14, 2011}}</ref> A Cube announced Oh Ha-young as the third member.<ref>{{cite news|title=\uc5d0\uc774\ud551\ud06c \ub9ac\ub354 \ucd08\ub871-\ub9c9\ub0b4 \ud558\uc601 \uc624\ubd93 \uc0ac\uc9c4 \uacf5\uac1c '\ubbf8\ubaa8 \ub0a8\ub2e4\ub974\ub124'| url=http://www.newsen.com/news_view.php?uid=201102231038231002|publisher=Newsen|date=February 23, 2011|accessdate=February 8, 2015}}</ref> In March, Jeong Eun-ji was introduced as the fourth member on A Cube's Twitter account through a video of her singing a rendition of [[Jennifer Hudson]]'s \"[[Love You I Do]]\".<ref>{{cite news|title=\uc5d0\uc774\ud551\ud06c \uc815\uc740\uc9c0 \ubbf8\ubaa8+\uac00\ucc3d\ub825, \ub124\ud2f0\uc98c \"\ub300\ubc15 \uc2e0\uc778 \ub098\ud0c0\ub0ac\ub2e4\" \uadf9\ucc2c| url=http://www.newsen.com/news_view.php?uid=201103101402021001| publisher=Newsen|date=March 10, 2013|accessdate=February 8, 2015}}</ref> Hong Yoo-kyung was similarly announced through an online video where she was playing the piano.<ref>{{cite news|title=\uc5d0\uc774\ud551\ud06c \ud074\ub798\uc2dd\uac78 \ud64d\uc720\uacbd \uae5c\uc9dd \uacf5\uac1c '\ub370\ubdd4\uace1 \uc2a4\ud3ec?'| url=http://www.newsen.com/news_view.php?uid=201103101632311002|publisher=Newsen|date=March 10, 2011|accessdate=February 8, 2015}}</ref> The last two members, Yoon Bo-mi and Kim Nam-joo, were introduced through the group's reality show, ''Apink News''.<ref>{{cite news|title=7\uc778\uc870 \uac78\uadf8\ub8f9 \uc5d0\uc774\ud551\ud06c, 11\uc77c \uc804 \uba64\ubc84 \uacf5\uac1c '\uac1c\ubd09\ubc15\ub450'| url=http://star.mk.co.kr/new/view.php?mc=ST&no=153443&year=2011|publisher=MK Media group|date=March 10, 2011|accessdate=February 8, 2015}}</ref>\n\nPrior to the group's debut, the documentary ''Apink News'' aired on the Korean cable channel Trend E.<ref>{{cite web|title=Apink News| url=http://apink.hyundaimedia.com/|publisher=Hyundai Media|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130928071143/http://apink.hyundaimedia.com/|archivedate=September 28, 2013|language=ko}}</ref> The show chronicled the launch process of Apink. The episodes were hosted by various celebrities, including [[G.NA]], Mario, [[MBLAQ]]'s Seung Ho and [[G.O (singer)|G.O]], Beast, [[4minute]], [[2AM (band)|2AM]]'s [[Jeong Jin Woon|Jinwoon]], [[Secret (South Korean band)|Secret]]'s [[Han Sunhwa|Sunhwa]] and [[Jun Hyoseong|Hyoseong]].<ref>{{cite news|title=\uc6a9\uc900\ud615 \uc190\ub3d9\uc6b4 \uc575\ucee4\ubcc0\uc2e0...\uc5d0\uc774\ud551\ud06c \uc801\ub098\ub77c \ubaa8\uc2b5 \ub300\uacf5\uac1c|url=http://www.newsen.com/news_view.php?uid=201104060902151002|publisher=Newsen|date=April 6, 2014|accessdate=February 8, 2015}}; {{cite news|title=\ud2b8\ub80c\ub514, \uc5d0\uc774\ud551\ud06c \ub370\ubdd4 \uc568\ubc94 \ucf58\uc149\ud2b8 TV \ucd5c\ucd08 \uacf5\uac1c|url=http://www.eto.co.kr/news/outview.asp?Code=20110414104955223&ts=205020|publisher=Economy Today|date=April 14, 2011|accessdate=February 8, 2015|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150208155734/http://www.eto.co.kr/news/outview.asp?Code=20110414104955223&ts=205020|archivedate=February 8, 2015|df=mdy-all}}; and {{cite news|title=\uc5d0\uc774\ud551\ud06c, '\uc5d0\uc774\ud551\ud06c \ub274\uc2a4'\uc11c \uc194\uc9c1 \ubc1c\ub784\ud55c \ubaa8\uc2b5 \uacf5\uac1c|url=http://starn.hankyung.com/news/index.html?no=1450|publisher=Starn|accessdate=February 8, 2015}}</ref><ref name=\"A Pink News\">{{cite news|title=\uc2e0\uc608 \uac78\uadf8\ub8f9 \uc5d0\uc774\ud551\ud06c, 24\uc2dc\uac04 \ub300\ubc29\ucd9c|url=http://sports.hankooki.com/lpage/music/201103/sp2011032311322395510.htm| publisher=Hankook|date=March 23, 2011|accessdate=February 8, 2015}}</ref> The week before Apink's official debut, they released their first television commercial for Ceylon Tea.<ref>{{cite news|title=\uc5d0\uc774\ud551\ud06c, \uc74c\ub8cc\uad11\uace0 \ubaa8\ub378 \ubc1c\ud0c1 |url=http://news.donga.com/3//20110411/36321364/1 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150208161429/http://news.donga.com/3//20110411/36321364/1 |url-status=dead |archive-date=February 8, 2015 |work=[[Dong-a Ilbo]] |date=April 11, 2014 |accessdate=February 15, 2015 }}</ref>\n\n=== 2011: ''Seven Springs of Apink'' and ''Snow Pink'' ===\n[[File:A Pink at the GSL Season 5 Code S Final Performance, 10 September 2011 03.jpg|thumb|A Pink at the [[Global StarCraft II League|GSL]] Season 5 Code S Final Performance, 2011]]\nThe group released their debut EP, ''[[Seven Springs of Apink]]'' and the music video for its lead single, \"Mollayo\" ({{lang|ko|\ubab0\ub77c\uc694}}; \"I Don't Know\"), on April 19, 2011. The album consists of five songs, including \"It Girl\" and \"Wishlist\". The music video for \"Mollayo\" featured Beast' [[Lee Gi-kwang]].<ref>{{cite news|author1=Kim Sang-yun|script-title=ko:\uc2e0\uc778\uadf8\ub8f9 \uc5d0\uc774\ud551\ud06c, \uc74c\uc6d0 \ubba4\uc9c1\ube44\ub514\uc624 \uacf5\uac1c\ub85c \uc0c1\ud07c\ubc1c\ub784 \ub9e4\ub825 \ubc1c\uc0b0| url=http://tvdaily.asiae.co.kr/read.php3?aid=1303177615151725003|date=April 19, 2011|accessdate=January 30, 2015|work=TV Daily| publisher=Asia Economy|language=ko}}</ref> Apink made their debut stage performance with \"Mollayo\" on Mnet's ''[[M Countdown]]'' on April 21 to promote their album.<ref>{{cite news|author1=Kim Su-ji|script-title=ko:'\uc5e0\uce74' \uc5d0\uc774\ud551\ud06c \uccab \ub370\ubdd4\ubb34\ub300 '\uc694\uc815\ub3cc\uc774 \ub5b4\ub2e4'| url=http://bntnews.hankyung.com/apps/news?popup=0&nid=04&c1=04&c2=04&c3=00&nkey=201104211729053&mode=sub_view|work=BNT News| publisher=Korea Economic Daily|accessdate=January 30, 2015|date=April 21, 2011|language=ko}}</ref> After several months of promoting \"Mollayo\", they began promoting \"It Girl\".<ref name=pastelcolors /> Apink also recorded the song \"Uri Geunyang Saranghage Haejuseyo\" ({{lang|ko|\uc6b0\ub9ac \uadf8\ub0e5 \uc0ac\ub791\ud558\uac8c \ud574\uc8fc\uc138\uc694}}; \"Please Let Us Love\") for the [[Seoul Broadcasting System|SBS]] drama, ''[[Protect the Boss]]'', the soundtrack of which was released in September 2011.<ref>{{cite news|title=\uc5d0\uc774\ud551\ud06c '\ubcf4\uc2a4\ub97c\uc9c0\ucf1c\ub77c' OST\ucc38\uc5ec \"\ub2ec\ucf64\ud55c \ub85c\ucf54\uc640 \ub531!\"|url=http://starn.hankyung.com/news/index.html?no=21074|publisher=The Starnn News|accessdate=February 8, 2015}}</ref>\n\nIn November 2011, Apink began recording a reality television show called ''[[Saturday Freedom#Birth of a Family|Birth of a Family]]'' with boy band [[Infinite (band)|Infinite]]. The show followed the efforts of the two idol groups to care for abandoned and mistreated animals over the course of eight weeks.<ref name=Birth>{{cite news|author1=Kim Yang-su|script-title=ko:\uc5d0\uc774\ud551\ud06c-\uc778\ud53c\ub2c8\ud2b8, '\uac00\uc871\uc758 \ud0c4\uc0dd' \ud569\ub958\u2026\uc720\uae30\uacac\uacfc \ub3d9\uac70\ub3d9\ub77d| url=http://joynews.inews24.com/php/news_view.php?g_menu=700200&g_serial=615312&rrf=nv|work=Joy News|publisher=inews24| accessdate=January 30, 2015|date=November 2, 2011|language=ko}}</ref>\n\nThe group released their second EP, ''Snow Pink'', on November 22, 2011, featuring the lead single \"My My\", a song composed by [[Shinsadong Tiger]]. Promotions for \"My My\" began on November 25 on [[Korean Broadcasting System|KBS]]' ''[[Music Bank (TV series)|Music Bank]]''.<ref>{{cite news|script-title=ko:\uc5d0\uc774\ud551\ud06c \ucef4\ubc31, \ub178\ucd9c\uc81c\ub85c-\uc21c\ub3c4100% \ubb34\uacf5\ud574 \uac78\uadf8\ub8f9|url=http://www.newsen.com/news_view.php?uid=201111251901001002| accessdate=January 30, 2015|work=Newsen|date=November 25, 2011|language=ko}}</ref> The promotions for \"My My\" included a one-day idol tea caf\u00e9, serving fans to raise profits for charity, where the group members prepared the food and drinks themselves. The members also auctioned off personal items for charity.<ref>{{cite news|author1=Park Yeong-ung|script-title=ko:\uc5d0\uc774\ud551\ud06c, \uc5f0\ub9d0 \ub9de\uc544 \uc77c\uc77c\ucc3b\uc9d1 \uac1c\uc5c5..\uc218\uc775\uae08 \uae30\ubd80|url=http://star.mt.co.kr/stview.php?no=2011121415354714473&type=3|accessdate=January 30, 2015| work=Star News|publisher=Money Today|date=December 14, 2011|language=ko}}</ref>\n\nStill in November, Apink received their first award, the \"Female Rookie Award\", at the [[2011 Mnet Asian Music Awards]] held in [[Singapore]]. In December 2011, Apink and Beast released a music video of the song \"Skinny Baby\" for school uniform brand Skoolooks.<ref>{{cite news|title=B2ST and A Pink Make School Uniforms Look Cool in 'Skinny Baby' Music Video|url=http://mwave.interest.me/enewsworld/en/article/2382/b2st-and-a-pink-make-school-uniforms-look-cool-in-skinny-baby-music-video|date=November 26, 2014|accessdate=February 8, 2015}}</ref> In January 2012, they received three more \"Rookie Awards\", at the Korean Culture & Entertainment Awards and the Golden Disk Awards held in [[Osaka]] and the High 1 Seoul Music Awards in Seoul.<ref>{{cite news|author1=Park HyunMin|title=A Pink Crowned Best Rookie of the Year| url=http://mwave.interest.me/enewsworld/en/article/2905/a-pink-crowned-best-rookie-of-the-year| work=enewsWorld| publisher=Mwave| date=January 20, 2015| accessdate=January 30, 2015}}</ref>\n\n===2012\u20132013: ''Une Ann\u00e9e'' and commercial success===\n[[File:Apink at Mnet 'M Countdown'.jpg|thumb|left|Apink performed \"Bubibu\" at Mnet ''M Countdown'' Smile Thailand Southeast Asia, 2012.]]\nIn January 2012, Apink won their first music show award on Mnet's ''M Countdown'' for \"My My\".<ref>{{cite news|author1=Oh MiJung| title=January 5, 2012: Cube Day|url=http://mwave.interest.me/enewsworld/en/article/2609/january-5-2012-cube-day|accessdate=January 30, 2015| work=enewsWorld| publisher=Mwave|date=January 6, 2012}}</ref> In February, they received the \"Rookie of the Year\" award at the 1st [[Gaon Chart Awards]].<ref>{{cite news|title=\uc18c\uc2dc\u00b7\uc544\uc774\uc720 \ub4f1 14\ud300, \uac00\uc628K\ud31d\uc5b4\uc6cc\ub4dc '\uac00\uc218\uc0c1'(\uc885\ud569)|url=http://entertain.naver.com/read?oid=108&aid=0002128423| publisher=MoneyToday|date=February 22, 2015|accessdate=February 9, 2015}}</ref> The group performed at the [[Canadian Music Fest]] in March 2012.<ref>{{cite news|title=Canada music fest signs Korean acts| url=http://koreajoongangdaily.joins.com/news/article/article.aspx?aid=2949411| accessdate=February 2, 2015| work=Korea JoongAng Daily|date=March 6, 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|author1=Fiona|title=CMF in Review: 2K12 Korea Night: K-Pop Wave at Kool Haus (03/21/12)|url=http://awmusic.ca/2012/03/22/cmf-in-review-2k12-korea-night-k-pop-wave-at-kool-haus-032112/|publisher=AW Music|accessdate=March 22, 2012|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131103190836/http://awmusic.ca/2012/03/22/cmf-in-review-2k12-korea-night-k-pop-wave-at-kool-haus-032112/|archivedate=November 3, 2013|df=mdy-all}}</ref> ''Apink News'' was continued for three seasons.<ref>{{cite news|title=\uc5d0\uc774\ud551\ud06c, '\uc5d0\uc774\ud551\ud06c \ub274\uc2a43'\uc11c \uc544\ub098\uc6b4\uc11c-PD\ub85c \u5927\ubcc0\uc2e0|url=http://www.eto.co.kr/news/outview.asp?Code=20120223125256657&ts=91646|publisher=Economy Today|date=February 21, 2012|accessdate=February 9, 2015|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150209214821/http://www.eto.co.kr/news/outview.asp?Code=20120223125256657&ts=91646|archivedate=February 9, 2015|df=mdy-all}}</ref> For season 3, which began to air in June 2012, Apink members contributed as writers, camera operators, directors, and in other production jobs.<ref name=Season3>{{cite news|title=\uc5d0\uc774\ud551\ud06c, '\uc5d0\uc774\ud551\ud06c \ub274\uc2a43'\uc11c \uc544\ub098\uc6b4\uc11c-PD\ub85c \u5927\ubcc0\uc2e0|url=http://osen.mt.co.kr/article/G1109420877| issue=June 21, 2012|publisher=Osen|accessdate=February 9, 2015}}</ref>\n\nThe group next released the eponymous \"April 19\" ({{lang|ko|4\uc6d4 19\uc77c}}) to celebrate their one-year anniversary. The song was composed by Kim Jin-hwan, with lyrics by the group's leader, Park Cho-rong.<ref name=\"chorong first song\">{{cite news|author1=Yun Seong Yeol|title=A Pink's Park Cho Rong dedicates her first written song to her fans|url=http://star.mt.co.kr/foreign/starViewEng.html?no=2012060214585284308| accessdate=February 2, 2015|work=Star News|date=June 2, 2012}}</ref> The song was included on their first studio album, ''[[Une Ann\u00e9e]]'', which was released on May 9, 2012. The group began promotion of the album with weekly appearances on music programs to perform the title song \"Hush\" through June.<ref>{{cite news|author1=Lee Hye-rin|url=http://news.nate.com/view/20120502n09201 |script-title=ko:'\uccad\uc21c\ub3cc \ub3cc\uc544\uc628\ub2e4!' \uc5d0\uc774\ud551\ud06c, 9\uc77c \uc815\uaddc1\uc9d1 \ubc1c\ud45c |date=May 2, 2012 |publisher=[[Nate (web portal)|Nate]] |work=OSEN |language=ko}}</ref> They continued to promote the album in July with the release of their third single from the album, \"Bubibu\". The single was chosen by fans through a poll on Mnet's website.<ref>{{cite news| author=Hong, Grace Danbi|title=A Pink to Follow Up with Fan-Picked 'Bubibu'|url=http://mwave.interest.me/enewsworld/en/article/8638/a-pink-to-follow-up-with-fan-picked-bubibu|accessdate=January 30, 2015|work=enewsWorld|publisher=Mwave|date=June 27, 2012}}</ref>\n\nIn January 2013, Apink recorded another single with Beast to promote Skoolooks. On January 5, at the AIA K-POP 2013 concert in Hong Kong, the group performed several of their songs along with other Cube Entertainment groups 4Minute and Beast.<ref>{{cite press release|title=AIA to Bring 'AIA K-POP 2013' to Hong Kong |url=http://www.aia.com.hk/en/resources/69daeb004d8cc327b24fb2aaf44b317c/AIAHK_press_release_20121122_eng_KPop.pdf |date=November 22, 2012 |publisher=AIA Hong Kong |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130125182723/http://aia.com.hk/en/resources/69daeb004d8cc327b24fb2aaf44b317c/AIAHK_press_release_20121122_eng_KPop.pdf |archivedate=January 25, 2013 }}</ref> In April 2013, Play M Entertainment released the statement that Hong Yoo-kyung left the group due to the educational schedules and Apink will continue as a six-piece group without adding new members.<ref>{{cite news|author1=Choi EunHwa|author2=Kim, Erika|title=A Pink\u2032s Hong Yoo Kyung Leaves Her Team|url=http://mwave.interest.me/enewsworld/en/article/34583/hong-yoo-kyung-leaves-a-pink-for-her-college-life| accessdate=January 30, 2015|work=enewsWorld|publisher=Mwave|date=April 23, 2014}}</ref>\n\nThe group's third EP, ''[[Secret Garden (Apink EP)|Secret Garden]]'', and music for its title track, \"[[No No No (Apink song)|NoNoNo]]\", were released on July 5, 2013.<ref>{{cite news|author1=Choi In-jeong|title=A Pink makes comeback with 3rd EP|url=http://www.koreaherald.com/view.php?ud=20130705000637| accessdate=February 2, 2015|work=The Korea Herald|date=July 5, 2013}}</ref> \"NoNoNo\" was the group's highest charting single, peaking at number 2 on ''Billboard'''s [[K-Pop Hot 100]].<ref>{{cite news|author1=Benjamin, Jeff|author2=Oak, Jessica| title=Davichi Earns Second K-Pop No. 1 Amid Label Shakeups|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/k-town/1569807/davichi-earns-second-k-pop-no-1-amid-label-shakeups| accessdate=February 4, 2015|work=Billboard|date=July 14, 2013}}</ref><ref>{{cite news| author1=Benjamin, Jeff| author2=Oak, Jessica|title=Ailee Nabs First Solo No. 1 on K-Pop Hot 100|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/k-town/4761631/ailee-nabs-first-solo-no-1-on-k-pop-hot-100|accessdate=February 4, 2015|work=Billboard|date=July 26, 2013}}</ref> In November 2013, at the [[2013 Mnet Asian Music Awards]], Apink received the Next Generation Global Star award.<ref>{{cite news|author1=Lee, Nancy|title=[2013 MAMA] G-Dragon Wins Artist of the Year, EXO Takes Album of the Year and Full List of Winners| url=http://mwave.interest.me/enewsworld/en/article/51585/2013-mama-g-dragon-wins-artist-of-the-year-exo-takes-album-of-the-year-and-full-list-of-winners| accessdate=January 30, 2015|work=enewsWorld|publisher=Mwave|date=November 22, 2013}}</ref> In December, Apink collaborated with Cube Entertainment acts Beast, 4Minute, [[BTOB]], G.NA, [[Roh Ji-hoon]], [[Shin Ji-hoon]] and Kim Kiri to release \"Christmas Song\".<ref>{{cite news|author=Hong, Grace Danbi|title=Cube and A Cube Artists Unite to Release Christmas Song Together| url=http://mwave.interest.me/enewsworld/en/article/52316/cube-and-acube-singers-gather-for-christmas|accessdate=January 30, 2015| work=enewsWorld| publisher=Mwave| date=December 2, 2013}}</ref> In the same month, they recorded a collaboration single with [[B.A.P (band)|B.A.P]], titled \"Mini\" for Skoolooks.<ref name=Skoolooks2013>{{cite web|author=Ryung, Hei|title=A Pink And B.A.P Rocks School Uniform Brand 'Skoolooks' MV| url=http://www.kpopstarz.com/articles/68183/20131203/a-pink-and-b-a-p-rocks-school-uniform-brand-skoolooks-mv.htm| website=KpopStarz| date=December 2, 2013}}</ref>\n\nIn July 2013, Apink were selected as honorary ambassadors for the Seoul Character & Licensing Fair 2013.<ref>{{cite web|title=Honorary Ambassador of Seoul Character & Licensing Fair 2013|url=http://www.bntnews.co.uk/app/news.php?nid=4822|website=BNTNews|accessdate=25 July 2015}}</ref>\n\n=== 2014-2016: Rise in popularity and Japanese debut===\n[[File:A Pink 2014 KBS Song Festival 2.jpg|thumb|250px|Apink at the 2014 KBS Song Festival red carpet]]\nOn January 13, 2014, Apink released \"Good Morning Baby\", a song composed by [[Duble Sidekick]], to celebrate the 1,000th day since the group's debut.<ref>{{cite news|author=Hong, Grace Danbi|title=A Pink Wishes Everyone a Good Morning in New MV|url=http://mwave.interest.me/enewsworld/en/article/55814/apink-releases-mv|accessdate=January 27, 2015|work=enewsWorld|publisher=Mwave|date=January 13, 2014}}</ref> The song peaked at number 6 on [[Gaon Music Chart|Gaon]]'s weekly chart.<ref>{{cite web|title=2014\ub144 04\uc8fc\ucc28 Digital Chart|url=http://gaonchart.co.kr/main/section/chart/online.gaon?nationGbn=T&serviceGbn=ALL&targetTime=04&hitYear=2014&termGbn=week|website=Gaon Chart| accessdate=February 5, 2015}}</ref> Their fourth EP, ''[[Pink Blossom]]'', and the music video for its title track, \"Mr. Chu\", by Duble Sidekick, were released on March 31.<ref>{{cite news|author1= Jung Ji Won|author2=Jung, Yeawon|title=A Pink's New Song 'Mr. Chu' Tops Real Time Music Charts|url=http://mwave.interest.me/enewsworld/en/article/62423/apink-ranks-number-one-with-its-new-song|date=March 31, 2014|accessdate=January 27, 2015|work=Newsen|publisher=Mwave}}</ref> The song peaked at number 2 on ''Billboard'''s K-Pop Hot 100.<ref name=\"billboard4-14\">{{cite news|author1=Benjamin, Jeff|author2=Oak, Jessica|title=K-Pop Hot 100: Park Hyo Shin Edges Out Apink|url=http://www.billboard.com/articles/columns/k-town/6052306/k-pop-hot-100-park-hyo-shin-edges-out-apink|work=Billboard|accessdate=February 5, 2015|date=April 15, 2014}}</ref> Apink won six music show trophies for \"Mr. Chu\",<ref name=\"Music Show Win 2014\"/> and the song was the eighth best selling digital song in 2014, according to Gaon's year-end chart.<ref>{{cite web|author=Kim Jin-u|script-title=ko:2014\ub144 \uc74c\uc545\uc2dc\uc7a5 \uacb0\uc0b0|trans-title=2014 Year-end Chart|url=http://gaonchart.co.kr/main/section/article/view.gaon?idx=8028&sgenre=opinion|website=Gaon Chart|date=January 15, 2015|accessdate=February 5, 2015|language=ko}}</ref>\n\nIn June 2014, Yoon Bomi and Kim Namjoo formed a sub-unit called Apink BnN, which released the single \"My Darling\" for [[Brave Brothers]]' 10th Anniversary Project.<ref name=\"Apink BnN\">{{cite news|author=Hong, Grace Danbi|title=Pink BnN to Sing 'My Darling' for Brave Brothers' 10th Anniversary Project|url=http://mwave.interest.me/enewsworld/en/article/69394/pinkbnn-works-with-bravebrothers|accessdate=January 26, 2015| work=enewsWorld| publisher=Mwave}}</ref> \"My Darling\" was later included on ''[[Pink Luv]]'', Apink's fifth EP. The single \"Break Up to Make Up\" for the project ''A Cube for Season #Sky Blue'', featuring Jeong Eunji and label mate [[Huh Gak]], was released on July 8, ranking first on Gaon's weekly digital chart.<ref>{{cite news|author1=Hong Jung Won|author2=Jung, Yeawon|title=Huh Gak and Jung Eun Ji's 'Break Up to Make Up' Immediately Rank No. 1 on Music Charts|url=http://mwave.interest.me/enewsworld/en/article/70274/huhgak-and-jungeunji-duet-take-over-music-charts| accessdate=February 2, 2015|work=Newsen|publisher=Mwave|date=July 9, 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|title=2014\ub144 29\uc8fc\ucc28 Digital Chart| url=http://gaonchart.co.kr/main/section/chart/online.gaon?nationGbn=T&serviceGbn=ALL&targetTime=29&hitYear=2014&termGbn=week| accessdate=February 2, 2015|work=Gaon Chart|publisher=Korea Music Content Industry Association|date=July 17, 2014}}</ref>\n\nIn August, Apink was chosen to replace Beast on MBC Every1's reality show, ''Showtime''.<ref>{{cite news|author=Jung Ji Won|title=A Pink Confirmed as Next Idol Group to Take Over 'Showtime'|url=http://mwave.interest.me/enewsworld/en/article/71133/apink-cast-as-next-idol-group-of-showtime|accessdate=February 5, 2015|date=July 18, 2014|work=Newsen| publisher=Mwave}}</ref> ''Apink's Showtime'' first aired on August 7, 2014, and there were a total of eight episodes. The show followed Apink's daily activities.<ref name=Showtime>{{cite news|author=Jung Ji Won|title=A Pink Promises to Run 10km Marathon with Fans if 'Showtime' Reaches Over 2% Rating|url=http://mwave.interest.me/enewsworld/en/article/71133/apink-cast-as-next-idol-group-of-showtime|date=July 18, 2014|accessdate=February 5, 2015|work=Newsen| publisher=Mwave}}</ref>\n\nApink debuted in Japan with a showcase on August 4 in [[Tokyo]] and on September 15 in Osaka with 6,000 fans in attendance.<ref>{{cite news| author1=Park Gyu-oh|title=Apink gains tremendous popularity in Japan| url=http://www.koreaherald.com/view.php?ud=20140915000803| accessdate=December 15, 2014|work=The Korea Herald|date=September 15, 2014}}</ref> Their first Japanese-language single, \"[[No No No (Apink song)|NoNoNo]]\", also including a Japanese version of \"My My\", was released on October 22.<ref>{{cite news|title=Apink tops Oricon preorder chart|url=http://www.kpopherald.com/view.php?ud=20140806000915_2|accessdate=February 5, 2015| work=K-Pop Herald| date=August 6, 2014}}</ref> The single was number 4 on Oricon's weekly singles chart.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.oricon.co.jp/rank/js/w/2014-11-03/|title=2014\u5e7410\u670820\u65e5\uff5e2014\u5e7410\u670826\u65e5 \u30aa\u30ea\u30b3\u30f3\u9031\u9593 \u30b7\u30f3\u30b0\u30eb\u30e9\u30f3\u30ad\u30f3\u30b0}}</ref> More than 20,000 fans reportedly gathered for their debut events held in three Japanese cities.<ref>{{cite news|author=Lee So Dam|title=A Pink Gathers Over 20,000 Fans at Japan Debut Events|url=http://mwave.interest.me/enewsworld/en/article/79041/a-pink-gathers-over-20000-fans-at-japan-debut-events|accessdate=February 5, 2015|date=October 24, 2014|work=Newsen|publisher=Mwave}}</ref>\n\nFrom September to November 2014, Apink raised funds for the Seungil Hope Foundation to build a hospital for [[ALS]] patients.<ref>{{cite news|author1=Park Gyu-oh|title=Apink's campaign for ALS exceeds goal on first day|url=http://www.kpopherald.com/view.php?ud=201409281649271762186_2|accessdate=December 1, 2014|work=K-pop Herald|date=September 28, 2014}}</ref> In November, Apink's online fan club surpassed 100,000 members.<ref>{{cite news|author=Park Gyu-oh|title=Apink's fan site members exceed 100,000|url=http://www.kpopherald.com/view.php?ud=20140923001058_2|accessdate=February 5, 2015|work=K-Pop Herald| date=September 23, 2014}}</ref> On November 13, Apink received the Best Female Dance award at the 6th [[MelOn Music Awards]] for their video of \"Mr. Chu\".<ref>{{cite news|author=Lee Hye-rin|script-title=ko:\ud0dc\uc591-\uc544\uc774\uc720-\uc9c0\uc624\ub514, '2014MMA' \ub300\uc0c1..\ube44\uc2a4\ud2b8-\uc704\ub108-\uc545\ub3d9\ubba4\uc9c0\uc158 2\uad00\uc655|trans-title=Taeyang-IU-god win '2014 MMA' Daesang... Beast, Winner, Akdong Musician awarded double crowns|url=http://osen.mt.co.kr/article/G1110008034| accessdate=January 27, 2015|work=OSEN|date=November 13, 2014|language=ko}}</ref>\n\nIn November 2014, the group released their fifth EP, ''Pink Luv'', as well as the music video for its title song, \"Luv\", which was composed by Shinsadong Tiger.<ref>{{cite news|author1=Ock Hyun-ju|title=Apink delays album release|url=http://www.kpopherald.com/view.php?ud=201411131736394479809_2|accessdate=December 1, 2014|work=K-pop Herald|date=November 13, 2014}}</ref> The song was Apink's first number 1 ranking on Gaon's weekly and monthly digital charts,<ref>{{cite web|author=Kim Jin-u|script-title=ko:12\uc6d4 \ucc28\ud2b8 \ub9ac\ubdf0|trans-title=December chart review|url=http://gaonchart.co.kr/main/section/article/view.gaon?idx=8061&sgenre=opinion|date=January 22, 2015|accessdate=February 5, 2015|website=Gaon Chart|publisher=Korea Music Content Industry Association|language=ko}}</ref> and ''Pink Luv'' topped Gaon's weekly album chart in its first week of release.<ref>{{cite web|script-title=ko:2014\ub144 49\uc8fc\ucc28 Album Chart|trans-title=Gaon Album Weekly Chart 4th week of November 2014|url=http://www.gaonchart.co.kr/main/section/chart/album.gaon?nationGbn=T&serviceGbn=&targetTime=49&hitYear=2014&termGbn=week|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20150205140009/http://www.gaonchart.co.kr/main/section/chart/album.gaon?nationGbn=T&serviceGbn=&targetTime=49&hitYear=2014&termGbn=week|archivedate=February 5, 2015|accessdate=February 5, 2015|language=ko}}</ref> Apink first performed \"Luv\" live at a showcase on November 20, followed by a performance of ''Music Bank'' the next day, prior to the album's release.<ref>{{cite news|author=Lee Min Ji|title=A Pink Promises to Sing at the Wedding of Uncle Fan If New Song Becomes No. 1|url=http://mwave.interest.me/enewsworld/en/article/81242/a-pink-promises-to-sing-at-the-wedding-of-uncle-fan-if-new-song-becomes-no-1|work=Newsen|accessdate=February 5, 2015|publisher=Mwave|date=November 20, 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite news| author1=Lee Min Ji|author2=Jung, Yeawon|title=A Pink Immediately Takes Over Music Charts with 'LUV'|url=http://mwave.interest.me/enewsworld/en/article/81388/a-pink-immediately-takes-over-music-charts-with-luv|accessdate=January 27, 2015|work=Newsen|publisher=Mwave| date=November 24, 2014}}</ref> The group won first place on all three major Korean music shows two weeks in a row, the only girl group to do so in 2014.<ref>{{cite news|last1=Lee|first1=Jinho| title=A Pink Becomes First Girl Group This Year to Place First in Three Music Programs for 2 Weeks|url=http://www.mnetamerica.com/news/article/83149/a-pink-becomes-first-girl-group-this-year-to-place-first-in-three-music-programs-for-2-weeks|accessdate=December 15, 2014|work=Mnet America}}</ref> Besides ''The Show'' and ''Music Core'', they also won a triple crown on ''Inkigayo'', which only allows three wins before removing a song from competition.<ref>{{cite news|author=Seon Mi-gyeong|script-title=ko:\uc5d0\uc774\ud551\ud06c, '\uc778\uac00' 3\uc8fc 1\uc704 \ud2b8\ub9ac\ud50c \ud06c\ub77c\uc6b4..12\uc6d4 \ud2b8\ub85c\ud53c \uc2f9\uc4f8\uc774|url=http://osen.mt.co.kr/article/G1110040398|accessdate=February 5, 2015|work=OSEN|date=December 28, 2014|language=ko}}</ref> They finished the year by winning all the music shows in December with \"Luv\".<ref name=\"Music Show Win 2014\">{{cite news|author=Kim JiYeon|title=A Pink Sweeps Music Program Trophies in December with \u2032LUV\u2032|url=http://mwave.interest.me/enewsworld/en/article/84006/a-pink-sweeps-music-program-trophies-in-december-with-luv| accessdate=February 5, 2015|work=enewsWorld|publisher=Mwave|date=December 29, 2014}}</ref> On Gaon's year-end ranking, Apink was the third best selling girl group in 2014.<ref>{{cite web|title=2014 Girl Group Ranking|url=http://gaonchart.co.kr/main/section/article/view.gaon?idx=7931&sgenre=opinion|website=Gaon Chart|accessdate=February 5, 2015}}</ref>\n\n[[File:Apink at Pink Paradise concert, 30 May 2015 03.jpg|left|thumb|300px|Apink during Pink Paradise in Shanghai]]\nOn January 10, 2015, Apink became the first group to win five consecutive awards on ''Music Core''.<ref>{{cite news|author=Im Jeong-yun|script-title=ko:\uc5d0\uc774\ud551\ud06c \uc190\ub098\uc740-\uae40\ub0a8\uc8fc, \uc74c\uc911 \uc5f0\uc18d1\uc704 \uccad\uc21c \uc778\uc99d\uc0f7 \"\uc0ac\ub791\ud574\uc694\"|url=http://www.newsen.com/news_view.php?uid=201501110824178110| accessdate=January 30, 2015|date=January 10, 2015|work=Newsen|language=ko}}</ref> The same month, the group received the \"Digital Bonsang\" and \"Best Female Performance Group\" awards at the 29th [[Golden Disk Awards]] in Beijing, \"Bonsang\" and \"Popularity\" awards at the [[Seoul Music Awards]], \"Best Female Group\" at the Korean Culture and Entertainment Awards and \"Best Single of December\" at the [[Gaon Chart K-Pop Awards]].<ref>{{cite news|author=Ock Hyun-ju|title=EXO, CNBLUE sweep Golden Disk Awards|url=http://www.koreaherald.com/view.php?ud=20150116000608|accessdate=January 30, 2015|work=The Korea Herald|date=January 16, 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|author=Kim Mi-hwa|script-title=ko:\uc5d0\uc774\ud551\ud06c, 4\ud68c \uac00\uc628K-POP \uc5b4\uc6cc\ub4dc \uc62c\ud574\uc758 \uac00\uc218\uc0c1..12\uc6d4 \uc74c\uc6d01\uc704|url=http://star.mt.co.kr/view/stview.php?no=2015012808433113071&type=1&outlink=1| accessdate=January 30, 2015|work=Star News|publisher=Money Today|date=January 28, 2015|language=ko}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|author=Gang Ji-ae|script-title=ko:\uc5d0\uc774\u